Subject: Re: [T2] engine install question

>I would try 2 things. One is make sure nothing is in the way for the
>engine to mate w/ the tranny. Two try putting the tranny in neutral
>(if not already) & turning the crank shaft a bit. sometimes helps.
>Three (I know I said two) make sure it's aligned correctly, especially
>up and down.

Also make sure you didn't let the engine droop thereby bending the lower 
bellhousing studs (on the engine). I did this with a Beetle 40 HP and spent 
a whole afternoon trying to figure this problem out.


